	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Questions and Answers.<br />
assuming there will be some rules questions.  will try coppying them here so its easier to find.<br />
<br />
<b>Do I have to pay upkeep for an army I buy this turn [2 gold to buy an army, 1 for upkeep]? If so that would use up the 3 gold right away.</b><br />
no. you pay upkeep at the beggining of the turn AFTER you've gotten your income for that turn. so this turn, you can get an army and still have 1 gold to spend on other stuff (like a caravan if you want).<br />
<br />
<b>Are ROPs allowed?</b><br />
No. Sorry.  ROP Rapes are too hard to manage.  You'll just have to &quot;invade&quot; allies. <img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Wink" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
<b>What should my orders look like?</b><br />
List the military units you're buying.  How many in which province (only those with citys and military bases can build units).<br />
if you're buying ships that could go into 2 sea territories, say which one.<br />
(and how many caravans/escorts you're gonna use if you want).<br />
<br />
moving orders for units.  again, you have to list each unit (or group if a lot are moving from same place to same place)<br />
if you're moving to any white provinces, put down if you want to claim them.<br />
<br />
list how many caravans you're sending to which nation (remember, not more then their nation's tax income)<br />
and how many escorts your sending to each (if any).<br />
<br />
your stealing instructions (how much you wanna steal from which nation in case they send caravans to your nation).<br />
<br />
<b>Can I disband armies and fleets i no longer want to use?</b><br />
yes.  but only if the unit isnt doing anything else that turn.  so if your orders say &quot;i have two armies in territory X.  diband one and attack with the other into.....&quot;, then its ok, but you cant say &quot;attack with the 2 armies and after the fight, disband them.<br />
<br />
<b>Can newly built fleets take on armies if the armies were built earlier?</b><br />
yes, the new fleet cant move (and cant unload armies cause it dont have any on it), but it can take &quot;veteran&quot; armies onboard.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
			<div>
				__________________<br />
				<a href="http://forums.civfanatics.com/showthread.php?t=55109" target="_blank">Mod</a> of <a href="http://forums.civfanatics.com/showthread.php?t=82680" target="_blank">Rnes5: To Trust a Thief</a><br />
Lesson: Don't attack countries for which the loss of an army bigger than your population is a temporary setback.  -  The Last Conformist
