	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				1. Do I have to pay upkeep for an army I buy this turn [2 gold to buy an army, 1 for upkeep]? If so that would use up the 3 gold right away.<br />
<br />
2. How do I make a profit on a caravan if I spend 1 gold to send it, 1 for an escort, and only get 2 gold back?
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div><br />
1. no.  you pay upkeep at the beggining of the turn AFTER you've gotten your income for that turn.  so this turn, you can get an army and still have 1 gold to spend on other stuff (like a caravan if you want).<br />
<br />
2.  if you spend 1 gold on a caravan and send it out without an escort,you'll get 2 gold the next turn.  once you're sending out more then one caravan (like 9 to a single nation) you can include some escorts some times to see if that nation is stealing from you.<br />
escorting this turn would be completely useless (even if you could afford it) since if your one caravan IS stolen, you'll know it anyway (wont get any income for it) so having the escort wont give you anything you didnt already have.  (that's always true if you're sending caravans to only 1 nation).</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
			<div>
				__________________<br />
				<a href="http://forums.civfanatics.com/showthread.php?t=55109" target="_blank">Mod</a> of <a href="http://forums.civfanatics.com/showthread.php?t=82680" target="_blank">Rnes5: To Trust a Thief</a><br />
Lesson: Don't attack countries for which the loss of an army bigger than your population is a temporary setback.  -  The Last Conformist
			</div>
		<!-- / sig -->
		
		
		
	
	</td>
