		<!-- message -->
		<div>So, if I understand this correctly, you don't pay upkeep on armies and navies that you buy this turn? In other words, you pay upkeep next turn when they can move, and every turn after that?<br />
<br />
The caravan system is still messed up <img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Wink" class="inlineimg" /> I'll never send a caravan with an escort, because I profit 0 if it comes back and I'm 2 gold in the red if someone steals it. Why bother? <br />
<br />
TO ALL<br />
Spain is not yet ready to make alliances but we wish to extend cordial relations to our neighbors England, France, and Italy.<br />
<br />
We would like to set up a trade agreement with all of you whereby each of us passes our caravans to someone else - in a circle. Thus risk is minimized because if someone's caravans are stolen they automatically know which country did it - so we don't need escorts. For example Spain sends caravans to Italy, who sends to England, who sends to France, who sends to Spain, etc.<br />
<br />
We should all have 1 gold free this turn so we can set up a trade round right now <img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Wink" class="inlineimg" /> does everyone agree? Please respond ASAP!</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
