	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>I would very much like to establish a trade agreement with England, France, Italy, etc. The goal of such an agreement would be to remove the risk of theft and allow everyone in the region to prosper by arranging a &quot;trade circle&quot;. Each nation would send ALL their caravans only to the next chain in the circle - thus if caravans are stolen their owner knows who stole them [so it's not necessary to send escorts]. The entire circle would pledge to punish anyone who steals caravans. <br />
<br />
The circle I envisioned was:<br />
<br />
Spain sends caravans to Italy.<br />
Italy sends caravans to England.<br />
England sends caravans to France.<br />
France sends caravans to Spain.<br />
<br />
Thus if Italy doesn't get all their money, they know England must have been stealing caravans. Then Spain, France, and Italy invade England <img src="images/smilies/biggrin.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Big Grin" class="inlineimg" /> Of course with the threat of war nobody will steal caravans and all our money will be safe.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
			<div>
				__________________<br />
